        <body>
            <p>
                <persName>L<add>?</add> Mayer</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Alwx Rhe<add>?</add></p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Philad</placeName>
                <date>July 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1862</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqr.</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Editor of the Occident</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sr</p>
            <p>The notice send for Publication, relative the Election of Officers in the<lb/> Germ
                Hebr. Congreg. Rodef Sholem, inserted in your valuable Journal<lb/> Vol XX Nr 4 Page
                184 having <sic>sufferd</sic> an entire mis-insertion, contrary to<lb/> notice send,
                which you will please correct in your next issue. As the<lb/> Members of the Board
                of Trustees were Elected previous the Election of Secty<lb/> Teacher and Sexton were
                held, the Publication <add>?</add> or to be, as transactions<lb/> took place.</p>
            <p>Also in your previous Occident it appears on a Local Items that<lb/>
                <persName>Moses Hirsch</persName> who died in the <placeName>Pa</placeName> Hospital
                was buried in the Mount<lb/> Sinai <sic>Cemetary</sic>, which <hi rend="underline"
                    >is incorrect</hi>. The decd was buried in the<lb/> Burial Grounds of the
                Congreg. Rodef Sholime<add>?</add>.</p>
            <p>Allow me, also, to bring to your attention an Editorial twice<lb/> in the
                    <add>?</add> Number of <date>July</date> Page 122, a Copy from <del>a
                    local</del><lb/>
                <del>Item</del>, the Leager of <date>June 21</date>, VL.III Nr 82 3d Page, under
                head<lb/> Local <add>?</add>, a “charitable and Praiseworthy
                <sic>Orginization</sic>.” why the<lb/> Editor left out all the words and sentiments
                after on the <date>4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of<lb/> July</date>. Enclosed please find
                the Ledger itself which contains<lb/> said insertions. May be, as the meeting, were
                held in the Synagogue<lb/> or the Congregation Rodef Sholem in <placeName>Juliana
                    Str.</placeName> It was <sic>intentionaly</sic><lb/> omitted. Further suggestion
                about this omission is left to your<lb/>
                <add>?</add>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">With all Resps.</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Rsr Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">L<add>?</add> Ellinger</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <placeName>119 Vine</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
